can hormone therapy itself cause cancer hormone therapy like tamoxifen or femara in treating breast cancer patients usually continues for several years is there any chance that these drugs can themselves cause cancer sure it can cause cancer the chances of having uterine cancer increases in females and prostate cancer in males but the benefit of using these drugs outweighs the risk therefore they are recommended and the patient during and after completion of the therapy should be on a regular follow up for recurrence and for any second cancer Cancer Prostate cancer Breast cancer Chemotherapy Endometrial cancer Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Radiation therapy Hormone replacement therapy Ovarian cancer Oncology Haloperidol Tocopherol Lung cancer Stomach cancer Colorectal cancer Cervical cancer History of cancer chemotherapy Androgen insensitivity syndrome Anabolic steroid Medical analysis of circumcision Metastasis Prolactinoma Testicular cancer Antiretroviral drug Hypertension Polycystic ovary syndrome Psoriasis Oral contraceptive Progesterone Adverse effect (medicine) Acromegaly Sex reassignment surgery female-to-male Infertility Malignant melanoma Orgasm Gynecomastia Obesity Abortion AIDS Endometriosis Gonadotropin-releasing hormone analog Renal cell carcinoma Alternative medicine Selective estrogen receptor modulator Growth hormone Doxepin Testosterone Post-traumatic stress disorder Stroke Baldness treatments Diazepam Bipolar disorder Maprotiline Urinary incontinence Hyperplasia Chlorpromazine Diabetes mellitus Herpes simplex virus Traumatic brain injury Thyroid cancer Clomipramine Brain tumor Menopause Clinical depression Electroconvulsive therapy Milk Osteoporosis Turner syndrome Graves-Basedow disease Migraine Aromatase inhibitor Cytomegalovirus COX-2 inhibitor Trazodone Publicly funded medicine Ataxia telangiectasia Mesothelioma Crohn's disease Chronic fatigue syndrome Schizophrenia Experimental cancer treatment Hypoglycemia Diarrhe